tasks.description:
In `src/llm.rs`, `run_llm_collect()` currently reads stdout (blocking until EOF) and stderr sequentially. If the subprocess writes more than ~64 KB to stderr before stdout EOF, the stderr pipe fills and the subprocess blocks, deadlocking.

Fix: spawn a background thread to drain stderr concurrently while the main thread reads stdout.

Replace the sequential stdout/stderr read block with:
```rust
// Read stderr concurrently to prevent pipe buffer deadlock.
let stderr_thread = stderr_handle.map(|mut stderr| {
    std::thread::spawn(move || {
        let mut s = String::new();
        let _ = stderr.read_to_string(&mut s);
        s
    })
});

let mut stdout_str = String::new();
if let Some(mut stdout) = stdout_handle {
    stdout
        .read_to_string(&mut stdout_str)
        .context("while reading stdout from llm.py")?;
}

let stderr_str = stderr_thread
    .and_then(|h| h.join().ok())
    .unwrap_or_default();
```

Remove the separate `let mut stderr_str` block that previously followed the stdout read. The rest of the function (`wait`, exit-code check) is unchanged.

Add `use std::io::Read as _;` is already present. No new imports required.

In `src/app.rs`, inside `run_pipeline_inner()`, immediately after the `run_transcription` call and before the LLM block, add:

```rust
if transcript.trim().is_empty() {
    anyhow::bail!(
        "No speech detected — recording may be too short or too quiet."
    );
}
```

This bails the pipeline before calling the LLM, preventing both observed failure modes:
- Empty transcript → 'I'm sorry' model response
- Empty transcript → empty LLM streaming response → whitespace clipboard

The bail message is user-facing (shown in the pipeline error alert). Keep it actionable.

The guard fires only when a prompt is selected (i.e., when the LLM would be called). If no prompt is selected, the transcript is passed directly to the clipboard — an empty transcript is acceptable there (the user records silence intentionally). Move the guard inside the `if !config.selected_prompt.is_empty()` block, before the `ollama_available()` check.

In `src/main.rs`, in the inline `llm.py` spawn block (CLI mode), resolve the log directory and pass it as `--log-dir`.

Before building `llm_cmd`, add:
```rust
let log_dir: Option<std::path::PathBuf> = dirs::home_dir()
    .map(|h| h.join(".config/yaptap/logs"));
```

In the `llm_cmd` builder, after `--provider`:
```rust
if let Some(ref dir) = log_dir {
    llm_cmd.arg("--log-dir").arg(dir);
}
```

Use `dirs::home_dir()` (the `dirs` crate is already a dependency).
